{
  "texts": [
    "Collection of field-scale yield data is particularly challenging, very expensive and error prone 64, 84.",
    "In some cases, such data are recorded in some form by farmers, farming equipment or equipment companies, but these data are not typically available to the public or research community.",
    "Despite the multi-dimensional importance of livestock to the livelihoods of at least 1.3 billion people, the critical role of the sector has never been reflected in development assistance, research outputs or the data landscape.",
    "From a data perspective, for instance, data collection approaches in livestock systems have not developed substantially over the past ~40 years (ref.",
    "64), although the methods of data collection have evolved (high-resolution remote sensing, drones, tablets and smartphones)."
  ]
}